Workstream 1
 
1.1 Azure Cost Management Platform Implementation
Objective: Establish Azure Cost Management & Billing as the primary cost visibility and control platform for AI workloads.
Key Actions:
Deploy Azure Cost Management & Billing Infrastructure
Configure cost analysis dashboards by service, resource group, and subscription scope
Set up budget thresholds and alerts for AI workload spending
Enable Copilot-enabled natural language cost analysis for easier querying
Integrate Azure Advisor recommendations into regular review cycles
Implement FinOps Framework Alignment
Map current Blip AI workloads to FinOps Framework capabilities
Incorporate AI-specific guidance for cost governance
Establish crawl-walk-run maturity assessment for FinOps capabilities
Owner: Microsoft FinOps Specialist or CSU resources + Blip FinOps Team
Dependencies: Azure subscription access, stakeholder alignment\ Timeline: Week 1
 
1.2 Tagging Strategy & Implementation
Objective: Deploy a comprehensive, enforceable tagging strategy that enables accurate cost allocation, chargeback models, and governance.
Key Actions:
Define Core Tag Schema
Implement mandatory financial tags across all AI workload subscriptions:
Cost Center: Align with Blip's financial structure for chargeback
Department: Organizational unit attribution
Environment: Production, Staging, Development, Testing
Project: Project-based cost tracking for ROI analysis
Application: Group resources by AI application/service
Owner: Establish accountability with contact information
Implement Tag Enforcement
Deploy Azure Policy to enforce mandatory tags and prevent untagged resource creation
Configure policy assignments with resource selectors for region-specific rules
Establish tag validation automation and compliance reporting
Enable Cost Allocation
Configure tag inheritance for resource groups and subscriptions
Set up cost analysis views grouped by tags for chargeback reports
Create department and project-level cost dashboards
Owner: Blip Cloud Infrastructure Team (Leonardo Nakasima) + Microsoft Governance Specialist\ Dependencies: Stakeholder agreement on tag schema, Azure Policy permissions\ Timeline: Week 1
 
1.3 Hub-and-Spoke Architecture Design
Objective: Structure subscriptions and projects using a hub-and-spoke model to improve governance, cost attribution, and scalability.
Key Actions:
Architecture Design Workshop
Design centralized hub for shared services (networking, security, monitoring)
Define spoke structure for AI workload isolation by project/team
Plan subscription hierarchy for clear cost attribution and P&L visibility
Governance Framework
Establish Azure Policy and RBAC model for hub-and-spoke governance
Define naming conventions aligned with tagging strategy
Create network segmentation and security boundaries
Documentation
Create architecture diagrams for hub-and-spoke model
Document subscription and resource group structure
Share via collaborative Google Doc
Owner: Microsoft Cloud Solutions Architect + Blip Cloud Architecture Team\ Dependencies: Agreement on organizational structure, networking requirements\ Timeline: Weeks 1